intermediate, or expert. Currently I do 30 minute intermediate, and find it 
is challenging for me. Clear instructions for a noob like me, no ads. One 
time purchase, and worth it. (I have bought it twice: once for ios and once 
for android.) I am pursuing yoga more intently but expect to get a lot more 
use from pocket yoga. Buy it!

You also spend about 4 minutes doing weird stuff like going back and forth between child's pose and upward facing dog.   If you've never done yoga before I definitely recommend against learning from an app, especially this one-- there is an index of poses and text describing how to do them, but no audio to guide you through it.
